              },
              "free_text": [
                " 10 MV TUNL FN tandem accelerator."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The beam energy was set using a set of high resolution",
                "90-90 dipole magnets, typical beam currents were",
                "100-200 enA of 3He+2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SPEC",
                "PPAC",
                "PROPC",
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The Split-pole spectrograph",
                " (SPS). The focal plane consists of two position",
                "sensitive avalanche counters, a dE proportionality",
                "counter, and a residual E scintillator."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "NaBr was selected as the target material. Targets",
                "were fabricated by using thermal evaporation to",
                "deposit a layer of NaBr on 22 microg/cm2 thick natC",
                "foils. A total of six targets were placed into the",
                "evaporator, and evaporation was halted once they",
                "reached a thickness of 70 microg/cm2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The 23Na(3He,d) 24Mg reaction was measured at",
                "angles between 3-21 degrees in steps of 2 degree with",
                "a field of 1.14-1.15 T. Additionally, the elastic",
                "scattering reaction, 23Na(3He,3He) , was measured at",
                "angles between 15-55 degrees in 5 degree steps and 59",
                "degree using fields of 0.75-0.80 T. The solid angle",
                "of the SPS was fixed throughout the experiment at SPS",
                "= 1.00(4) msr. After the reaction products were",
                "momentum to charge analyzed by the spectrograph, they",
                "were detected at the focal plane of the SPS."
              ]
            }
          ],
